This is the best restaurant in the area for a quick bite to eat. The food all tastes of high quality, and there is a lot of variety in an easy to comprehend menu. They serve mainly burritos, but you can also get salads, soups, and smoothies. It's a great place to go before a movie, as you can easily hide a burrito in a pocket or under a coat as you walk into the movie theater. There sizes are quite good considering the very low price of eating at Boloco. All in all, it is a great restaurant that should be visited frequently.
